@ScottSwezey @davegandy We'd love to serve you Dave. Whether a company is one person or many people, we're here to help.
@LisaFalzone @ericlmartineau @CooperASmith It was fun! Always a privilege to share advice with aspiring entrepreneurs. #PayItForward
ex. people don't celebrate getting a mortgage, they celebrate the house (and paying off the mortgage). #StartupTips
Fundraising is not the goal. It's an enabler of reaching a goal. #StartupTips
Fundraising is the same as hiring. Be deliberate and intentional. Get to know the person since you'll spend years together. #StartupTips
Mission Driven = focusing on the long term. Near term goals/metrics are important but they must build toward a sustainable and scalable biz.
Someone should start a company when they care so much about an unsolved problem that they're forced to start a biz to do something about it.
Mission Driven = being proud of *how* a goal is achieved, not just achieving it. #StartupTips
Mission Driven = solving a problem by creating a business. Not vice versa. #StartupTips
First principles thinking and pattern matching are both important in a startup. The key is choosing which to apply, and when. #StartupTips
Nothing is ever done in a startup. It can always be improved or done better. #StartupTips
When a company grows, the same role at a larger scale becomes a different role. The key is constant improvement and learning.
Your job as a founder is to keep firing yourself from as many jobs as you can (by hiring and empowering your teammates). #StartupTips
Hiring (at Gusto) is about (1) aligned values, (2) shared motivations, (3) relevant skills. Define what matters to you. #StartupTips
Hiring should never be easy. If it is, then it's being done wrong. #StartupTips
Culture scales by (1) always focusing on hiring right, and (2) empowering your teammates to lead by example for others.
People don't have separate personal values and professional values. It's one value system that's who they are. Stay true to it.
company values should never be printed on a wall. you either live them or you don't.
Culture means being opinionated. tip: define your company values in your first six months. they can then guide how you hire.
Know anyone in SF or Denver that wants to join a mission driven business, being built for the long term? join us. https://t.co/cXyVJscxW6
